  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-8 clean, bounded envelope)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors scoped-out or not-applicable (acceptable at MRL 2). ContextOfUse declares concrete hasOperatingEnvelope (flow 1–7 L/min, speed 1500–3500 RPM, inlet pressure 5–15 mmHg, haematocrit 35–45%) and hasApplicabilityConstraint (adult CPB patients, single-stage centrifugal pump geometry). Validation datasets cover boundary operating points. Negative-control package: no weakener should fire.",
